00:12:52,359 --> 00:12:54,817
Imagine how impressed I'll be
when you get an indictment.

233
00:12:55,692 --> 00:12:57,442
- There's a bigger question.
- Which is?

234
00:12:57,525 --> 00:13:01,359
Who started the riots?
Was it the protesters or the police?

235
00:13:01,442 --> 00:13:04,650
- The police don't start riots.
- They'll have witnesses who say they did.

236
00:13:04,734 --> 00:13:06,859
And you'll dismantle them and win,

237
00:13:06,942 --> 00:13:10,192
because, Mr. Schultz,
that's what's expected of you.

238
00:13:12,859 --> 00:13:15,359
You didn't show
a lot of gratitude in there.

239
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:20,734
On top of everything, we're giving them
what they want: a stage and an audience.

240
00:13:21,359 --> 00:13:23,484
You think there's gonna be a big audience?

241
00:13:23,567 --> 00:13:27,109
The whole world is watching!

242
00:13:27,192 --> 00:13:28,442
Yes, sir, I do.

243
00:13:29,150 --> 00:13:33,567
The whole world is watching!

244
00:13:34,609 --> 00:13:37,442
- Traitors!
- Lock up the longhairs!

245
00:13:37,525 --> 00:13:39,525
Power to the people!

246
00:13:39,609 --> 00:13:41,067
No more war!

247
00:13:44,109 --> 00:13:47,442
The whole world is watching!

248
00:13:48,025 --> 00:13:50,567
Get out! How dare you? Get out!

249
00:13:51,567 --> 00:13:53,067
- Abbie!
- Are you all right?

250
00:13:53,150 --> 00:13:54,275
Abbie, over here.

251
00:13:54,359 --> 00:13:57,692
- I was, until I saw that.
- Most of them are on our side.

252
00:13:57,775 --> 00:13:59,859
- We love you, Abbie!
- See?

253
00:14:01,067 --> 00:14:01,900
Watch out!

254
00:14:01,984 --> 00:14:04,734
Jesus Christ!
How did you do that?

255
00:14:05,609 --> 00:14:06,609
Experience.

256
00:14:06,692 --> 00:14:09,692
Abbie, right over here!

257
00:14:09,775 --> 00:14:11,192
Over here! Over here!

258
00:14:11,275 --> 00:14:13,150
You don't know what to do
with the egg now?

259
00:14:13,234 --> 00:14:14,234
No.

260
00:14:16,192 --> 00:14:19,734
- Mr. Kunstler, one question!
- Bill! Bill!

261
00:14:19,817 --> 00:14:22,400
All right. Hang on. Quiet down.

262
00:14:22,484 --> 00:14:25,942
I want you all to meet
a new addition to the defense team.

263
00:14:26,025 --> 00:14:28,150
This is Leonard Weinglass,

264
00:14:28,234 --> 00:14:31,442
one of this country's most
talented First Amendment litigators.

265
00:14:31,525 --> 00:14:33,984
- Bill, can you tell us--
- Go ahead, Sy.

266
00:14:34,067 --> 00:14:35,525
What's the status of Charles Garry?

267
00:14:35,609 --> 00:14:38,359
Charles Garry is still in the hospital.

268
00:14:38,442 --> 00:14:41,359
You should contact his office
for information.

269
00:14:41,442 --> 00:14:42,942
- One more.
- Marjorie.

270
00:14:43,025 --> 00:14:44,775
You're representing Bobby Seale today?

271
00:14:44,859 --> 00:14:48,817
Oh, no, it's very important
that it be understood that, uh,

272
00:14:48,900 --> 00:14:51,525
for his own protection,
his own protection,

273
00:14:51,609 --> 00:14:54,525
I will not be acting as
Bobby Seale's attorney today.

274
00:14:54,609 --> 00:14:55,442
One more. Jack.

275
00:14:55,525 --> 00:14:59,275
I was told that Hayden was the one
who wanted to bring Mr. Weinglass in,

276
00:14:59,359 --> 00:15:02,025
that Hayden has concerns
about your seriousness.

277
00:15:02,109 --> 00:15:04,609
- Well...
- This is William Kunstler.

278
00:15:04,692 --> 00:15:07,817
You wanna find out how serious he is,
meet him at a witness stand.

279
00:15:42,275 --> 00:15:45,442
I understand why they're tryin'
to smoke Abbie, Jerry and Hayden,

280
00:15:45,525 --> 00:15:46,859
even Rennie and Dellinger,

281
00:15:46,942 --> 00:15:49,817
but I can't figure out
what the two of us are doin' here.

282
00:15:49,900 --> 00:15:53,692
I feel exactly the same way, but
this is the Academy Awards of protests,

283
00:15:53,775 --> 00:15:57,025
and as far as I'm concerned,
it's an honor just to be nominated.

284
00:15:58,484 --> 00:15:59,484
What is that?

285
00:16:00,317 --> 00:16:02,025
I've been keeping a list every day.

286
00:16:02,567 --> 00:16:05,567
Americans who've been killed
since the day we were arrested.

287
00:16:05,650 --> 00:16:06,650
Why?

288
00:16:07,275 --> 00:16:10,942
With the trial starting, it might get easy
to forget who this is about.

289
00:16:18,275 --> 00:16:19,650
- Fellas.
- Morning.

290
00:16:19,734 --> 00:16:20,734
Good morning.

291
00:16:26,525 --> 00:16:29,567
I just got a question
about my seriousness.

292
00:16:30,109 --> 00:16:34,609
Whatever's going on between you and Abbie,
could you keep it out of this building?

293
00:16:34,692 --> 00:16:37,692
I got a feeling this is gearing up to be...

294
00:17:01,234 --> 00:17:03,150
- Fred.
- Bill.

295
00:17:03,900 --> 00:17:05,817
Did you have breakfast this morning?

296
00:17:08,192 --> 00:17:10,234
- What?
- Did you have breakfast?

297
00:17:10,859 --> 00:17:13,234
- I did.
- Well, what'd you have?

298
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:14,900
What are you doin'?

299
00:17:14,942 --> 00:17:16,484
I'm talkin' to him about breakfast

300
00:17:16,567 --> 00:17:19,109
because that's all I'm allowed
to talk to him about.

301
00:17:19,192 --> 00:17:20,192
That's right.

302
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:23,942
- Bobby--
- We have instructions from our lawyer.

303
00:17:24,025 --> 00:17:26,692
If you need me, I'm sittin' right there.

304
00:17:26,775 --> 00:17:29,692
You just look at me
and you say, "I need you."

305
00:17:30,650 --> 00:17:33,317
- We don't need you, Bill.
- You two gonna be like this?

306
00:17:34,775 --> 00:17:38,192
Your friends shouldn't sit together.
The jury's not gonna like that.

307
00:17:38,275 --> 00:17:40,067
This isn't my jury.
If they don't like it--

308
00:17:40,150 --> 00:17:41,192
No, he's right.

309
00:17:44,734 --> 00:17:47,900
Spread out, okay? In pairs.

310
00:17:48,442 --> 00:17:49,525
And Fred?

311
00:17:50,900 --> 00:17:53,275
- No, they're dressed just fine.
- It's all right.

312
00:17:54,025 --> 00:17:56,609
And take your very scary hats off.

313
00:18:01,650 --> 00:18:02,650
Don't mess this up.

314
00:18:04,567 --> 00:18:06,817
All right. Good pep talk.

315
00:18:10,984 --> 00:18:11,984
Hey!

316
00:18:14,984 --> 00:18:16,275
You see the crowd out there?

317
00:18:17,234 --> 00:18:18,442
I have an egg.

318
00:18:18,525 --> 00:18:20,859
- Get rid of that.
- You don't think I want to?

319
00:18:20,942 --> 00:18:23,692
It's like we're... What's his name?
We just met him.

320
00:18:23,775 --> 00:18:25,734
- Yeah.
- What is his name?

321
00:18:25,817 --> 00:18:28,317
- Who?
- The drummer. The greatest drummer ever.

322
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:29,234
Gene Krupa?

323
00:18:29,317 --> 00:18:32,109
No. Gene Krupa? I'm talkin' about
the drummer from Cream.

324
00:18:32,192 --> 00:18:33,609
We just met him last night.

325
00:18:33,692 --> 00:18:35,609
- Ginger Baker.
- Thank you.

326
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:39,650
Crowd outside is so big, it's as if
we're Ginger Baker, I was trying to say.

327
00:18:39,734 --> 00:18:42,859
- Are you stoned?
- Yeah. You?

328
00:18:44,359 --> 00:18:45,359
All right, sit down.

329
00:18:48,942 --> 00:18:50,400
You remember what I said.

330
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:53,650
Okay, and you remember
to keep us out of prison.

331
00:18:54,317 --> 00:18:56,567
There's a lot of good advice this morning.

332
00:18:56,650 --> 00:18:57,692
All rise.

333
00:19:05,525 --> 00:19:10,484
Hear ye, hear ye.
September 26th, 1969, ten o'clock a.m.

334
00:19:10,567 --> 00:19:13,359
All persons having business
before the United States District Court

335
00:19:13,442 --> 00:19:15,817
of Northern Illinois,
Southern District, Eastern Division,

336
00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:17,775
draw near and ye shall be heard.

337
00:19:17,859 --> 00:19:19,859
Judge Julius Hoffman presiding.

338
00:19:19,942 --> 00:19:22,775
God save the United States of America
and this Honorable Court.

339
00:19:22,859 --> 00:19:24,067
Be seated.

340
00:19:26,275 --> 00:19:29,650
Mr. Marshal, bring in our jury.

341
00:19:41,317 --> 00:19:44,442
Let the record show
that we have been joined

342
00:19:44,525 --> 00:19:48,067
by our 12 jurors and four alternates.

343
00:19:48,150 --> 00:19:50,484
Good morning, ladies and gentlemen.

344
00:19:51,025 --> 00:19:52,025
Good morning.

345
00:19:52,650 --> 00:19:55,734
Mrs. Winter, please call the case.

346
00:19:55,817 --> 00:19:58,734
69 CR 180,

347
00:19:58,817 --> 00:20:03,359
United States of America
vs. David Dellinger,

348
00:20:03,442 --> 00:20:06,525
Rennard C. Davis, Thomas Hayden,

349
00:20:06,609 --> 00:20:09,775
Abbott Hoffman, Jerry C. Rubin,

350
00:20:09,859 --> 00:20:15,609
Lee Weiner, John R. Froines
and Bobby G. Seale for trial.

351
00:20:15,692 --> 00:20:18,025
Are the People ready
to make opening arguments?

352
00:20:18,109 --> 00:20:19,109
We are, Your Honor.

353
00:20:19,150 --> 00:20:22,359
- I don't have my lawyer here.
- It's not your turn to speak.

354
00:20:22,442 --> 00:20:24,234
My trial's begun without my lawyer.

355
00:20:24,317 --> 00:20:26,817
Please sit.

356
00:20:31,859 --> 00:20:32,859
Mr. Schultz?

357
00:20:36,025 --> 00:20:38,525
Good morning.
My name is Richard Schultz.

358
00:20:38,609 --> 00:20:41,609
I'm an assistant US attorney
for the Southern District of Illinois.

359
00:20:41,692 --> 00:20:44,567
Seated at my table is my boss,
US Attorney Thomas Foran.

360
00:20:44,650 --> 00:20:46,942
Or you could say, I'm seated at his table.

361
00:20:48,359 --> 00:20:50,900
At the defense table
are the eight defendants

362
00:20:50,984 --> 00:20:54,442
represented by their lawyers
William Kunstler, Leonard Weinglass.

363
00:20:55,442 --> 00:20:59,692
Now, the defendants would tell you that
they represent three different groups.

364
00:20:59,775 --> 00:21:02,359
- They would tell you that one group is--
- Excuse me.

365
00:21:03,150 --> 00:21:03,984
Yes, sir.

366
00:21:04,067 --> 00:21:07,192
I'd like to clarify something
for the jurors.

367
00:21:07,275 --> 00:21:10,025
There are two Hoffmans in this courtroom.

368
00:21:10,109 --> 00:21:14,775
The defendant Abbie Hoffman
and myself, Judge Julius Hoffman.

369
00:21:15,734 --> 00:21:16,567
Thank you, sir.

370
00:21:16,650 --> 00:21:19,150
I didn't want there to be
confusion on the matter.

371
00:21:19,234 --> 00:21:21,484
Man, I don't think
they're gonna mix us up.

372
00:21:23,067 --> 00:21:25,817
You will address this court
as Judge or Your Honor,

373
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:28,817
and you will not
address this court until...

374
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:30,650
You will not address this court!

375
00:21:33,275 --> 00:21:36,234
The defendants would tell you
they represent three different groups.

376
00:21:36,317 --> 00:21:38,484
And the record should reflect

377
00:21:38,567 --> 00:21:42,567
that defendant Hoffman and I
are not related.

378
00:21:42,650 --> 00:21:44,067
Father, no!

379
00:21:45,567 --> 00:21:48,692
Mr. Hoffman, are you familiar
with contempt of court?

380
00:21:49,359 --> 00:21:52,525
It's practically a religion for me, sir.

381
00:21:53,775 --> 00:21:55,734
- Your Honor?
- Continue.

382
00:21:59,067 --> 00:22:02,484
Rennie Davis and Tom Hayden
are the leaders of the SDS,

383
00:22:02,567 --> 00:22:04,359
Students for a Democratic Society.

384
00:22:04,984 --> 00:22:07,692
Davis and Hayden
brought their people to Chicago

385
00:22:07,775 --> 00:22:10,484
for the purpose
of causing violence in the streets

386
00:22:10,567 --> 00:22:13,150
in order to disrupt
the Democratic Convention.

387
00:22:13,234 --> 00:22:16,109
You know the Youth International Party
as the Yippies.

388
00:22:16,859 --> 00:22:19,525
Their leaders are
Abbie Hoffman and Jerry Rubin.

389
00:22:19,609 --> 00:22:22,984
Bobby Seale is the leader
of the Black Panther Party.

390
00:22:23,567 --> 00:22:27,400
Again, the defendants would tell you
that these are three distinct groups.

391
00:22:27,484 --> 00:22:29,317
- But they all--
- Excuse me.

392
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:30,234
Yes.

393
00:22:30,317 --> 00:22:32,442
- May I speak?
- No, sir.

394
00:22:32,525 --> 00:22:33,609
He just said my name.

395
00:22:33,692 --> 00:22:37,442
You're a defendant in this case.
You're likely to hear your name.

396
00:22:37,525 --> 00:22:41,275
I have a right to counsel,
and His Honor knows that.

397
00:22:41,359 --> 00:22:45,525
Don't tell the court what it does
and does not know. Be seated.

398
00:22:48,859 --> 00:22:50,234
Mr. Schultz.

399
00:22:54,192 --> 00:22:55,609
The radical left. That's all.

400
00:22:55,692 --> 00:22:57,734
They're the radical left
in different costumes.

401
00:22:57,817 --> 00:22:59,567
These defendants had a plan,

402
00:22:59,650 --> 00:23:02,484
and a plan among two or more people
is a conspiracy.

403
00:23:03,067 --> 00:23:05,692
The defendants crossed state lines
to execute their plan.

404
00:23:05,775 --> 00:23:09,317
That's why we're in federal court,
and the plan was to incite a riot,

405
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:11,734
and there's one thing you already know.

406
00:23:12,484 --> 00:23:13,567
They succeeded.

407
00:23:13,650 --> 00:23:18,692
Excuse me. Have we identified
the other defendants for the record?

408
00:23:19,525 --> 00:23:21,192
A Mr... Wiener.

409
00:23:21,817 --> 00:23:22,650
Weiner.

410
00:23:22,734 --> 00:23:25,234
Mr. Froines and Mr. Dillinger.

411
00:23:25,317 --> 00:23:26,442
Dellinger, Your Honor.

412
00:23:27,192 --> 00:23:28,275
What's going on here?

413
00:23:28,359 --> 00:23:30,734
Uh, you're referring
to the defendant Dellinger.

414
00:23:30,817 --> 00:23:34,067
- Derringer.
- Um, it's Dellinger, sir.

415
00:23:34,150 --> 00:23:39,275
Note the prosecution was referring
to the defendant Derringer.

416
00:23:39,359 --> 00:23:41,900
- Not Dellinger.
- It is Dellinger, Your Honor.

417
00:23:41,984 --> 00:23:43,900
Can we straighten this out?

418
00:23:43,984 --> 00:23:47,817
Sure. Dillinger was a bank robber.
Derringer is a gun.

419
00:23:47,900 --> 00:23:50,900
He's David Dellinger,
and the judge and I are not related.

420
00:23:50,984 --> 00:23:54,484
Your Honor, I'd like to caution the court
that this kind of disruption

421
00:23:54,567 --> 00:23:58,150
and display of disrespect
will be a continuing tactic for defense.

422
00:23:58,234 --> 00:24:00,484
Sir, it's not a tactic.
At the moment,

423
00:24:00,567 --> 00:24:03,734
the defendants are the only ones
on record as knowing their own names.

424
00:24:03,817 --> 00:24:05,567
Be seated, Mr. Schultz...

425
00:24:05,650 --> 00:24:07,817
Uh, Mr. Kunstler.

426
00:24:09,859 --> 00:24:12,275
I object to being characterized
as a member of this group.

427
00:24:12,359 --> 00:24:14,692
- Who is your lawyer?
- Charles R. Garry.

428
00:24:14,775 --> 00:24:16,609
Is Mr. Garry here today?

429
00:24:16,692 --> 00:24:18,067
- No, he is not.
- Your Honor--

430
00:24:18,150 --> 00:24:19,692
Are you representing Mr. Seale?

431
00:24:19,775 --> 00:24:21,525
- No, sir.
- Then, sit.

432
00:24:23,484 --> 00:24:26,067
Mr. Schultz, forgive me.

433
00:24:26,609 --> 00:24:28,775
Have you concluded your opening statement?

434
00:24:29,692 --> 00:24:30,817
Yes, Your Honor.

435
00:24:30,900 --> 00:24:33,567
My lawyer Charles Garry
is in a hospital in Oakland

436
00:24:33,650 --> 00:24:35,525
having undergone gallbladder surgery.

437
00:24:35,609 --> 00:24:36,775
Mr. Kunstler.

438
00:24:37,484 --> 00:24:39,650
You are sitting right next to the man.

439
00:24:39,734 --> 00:24:42,109
Just represent him.
It's the same case.

440
00:24:42,192 --> 00:24:45,025
The fact that there's a lawyer near Mr. Seale

441
00:24:45,109 --> 00:24:47,609
does not satisfy
the requirements of due process.

442
00:24:47,692 --> 00:24:48,775
I have a right--

443
00:24:48,859 --> 00:24:53,817
A motion was made for postponement
due to Mr. Garry's medical condition.

444
00:24:53,900 --> 00:24:56,609
I was there.
Your Honor denied that motion.

445
00:24:56,692 --> 00:24:59,775
Therefore, Mr. Seale is here
without legal representation.

446
00:24:59,859 --> 00:25:04,650
I don't care
for your general tone, Mr. Kunstler.

447
00:25:04,734 --> 00:25:07,025
I meant no disrespect to the court.

448
00:25:07,109 --> 00:25:11,567
I'm trying to be clear that I can't muddy
Mr. Seale's grounds for appeal

449
00:25:11,650 --> 00:25:13,484
by appearing to speak as his lawyer.

450
00:25:13,567 --> 00:25:17,025
I don't ask you to compromise
Mr. Seale's position, sir.

451
00:25:17,109 --> 00:25:21,400
But I will not permit him
to address the jury

452
00:25:21,484 --> 00:25:23,942
when his perfectly competent lawyer
is sitting--

453
00:25:24,025 --> 00:25:26,400
For the fourth time,
he's not Bobby's lawyer.

454
00:25:28,817 --> 00:25:31,275
You're, uh... Mr. Rubin.

455
00:25:31,942 --> 00:25:33,025
Yes, sir.

456
00:25:33,109 --> 00:25:34,567
Don't ever do that again!

457
00:25:37,317 --> 00:25:39,150
Your Honor,
I'm not with these guys.

458
00:25:39,234 --> 00:25:42,234
I never met most of them
until the indictment.

459
00:25:42,317 --> 00:25:44,650
- We will have order.
- There are eight of us here.

460
00:25:44,734 --> 00:25:48,692
There are signs out there that read,
"Free the Chicago 7." I'm not with them!

461
00:25:48,775 --> 00:25:52,775
- Mr. Marshal, will you seat Mr. Seale?
- Conspiracy? I never met most of them.

462
00:25:52,859 --> 00:25:56,484
Frankly, the US attorney wanted
a Negro defendant to scare the jury.

463
00:25:56,567 --> 00:25:58,984
I was thrown in
to make the group look scarier.

464
00:25:59,067 --> 00:26:01,109
I came to Chicago.
I made a speech!

465
00:26:01,192 --> 00:26:02,942
- Mr. Seale--
- I had a chicken pot pie,

466
00:26:03,025 --> 00:26:05,359
went to the airport
and I flew back to Oakland,

467
00:26:05,442 --> 00:26:06,984
that's why they call it the Chicago...

468
00:26:07,067 --> 00:26:08,900
Get your hands off me!

469
00:26:08,984 --> 00:26:12,817
Charge Mr. Seale
with one count of contempt of court.

470
00:26:38,525 --> 00:26:40,192
We have to make a decision right now,

471
00:26:40,275 --> 00:26:44,317
a decision I assumed we'd already made
four months ago when trial prep began.

472
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:48,650
Are we using this trial to defend
ourselves against very serious charges

473
00:26:48,734 --> 00:26:50,484
that could land us in prison
for ten years?

474
00:26:51,567 --> 00:26:54,484
Or to say a pointless "fuck you"
to the establishment?

475
00:26:54,567 --> 00:26:57,650
