495
00:27:52,484 --> 00:27:54,609
I don't have a problem
with what we look like.

496
00:27:54,692 --> 00:27:57,275
Jerry likes what we look like.
Uh, John?

497
00:27:57,359 --> 00:27:58,442
- Lee?
- Yeah.

498
00:27:58,525 --> 00:28:02,109
- I feel like I'm ten pounds too heavy.
- I don't like it when we fight.

499
00:28:02,192 --> 00:28:03,984
- Rennie?
- Tom should be heard.

500
00:28:04,067 --> 00:28:05,067
And he was.

501
00:28:05,609 --> 00:28:10,109
When we walked in here, they were chanting
that the whole world is watching.

502
00:28:10,192 --> 00:28:11,900
This is it. We're on.

503
00:28:11,984 --> 00:28:16,150
This is what revolution looks like.
Real revolution. Cultural revolution.

504
00:28:16,234 --> 00:28:17,775
Why did you come here?

505
00:28:17,859 --> 00:28:19,775
I got an invitation from a grand jury.

506
00:28:19,859 --> 00:28:21,900
Last summer.
Why did you come to the convention?

507
00:28:22,900 --> 00:28:24,400
To end the war.

508
00:28:24,484 --> 00:28:26,734
Guys, before you tether yourselves
to this man,

509
00:28:26,817 --> 00:28:30,234
just know the very last thing he wants
is for the war to end.

510
00:28:30,317 --> 00:28:35,317
I don't have time for cultural revolution.
It distracts from actual revolution.

511
00:28:35,400 --> 00:28:37,234
All right, all right, all right.

512
00:28:37,317 --> 00:28:39,234
But you got time for a haircut.

513
00:28:39,317 --> 00:28:41,234
