552
00:30:41,942 --> 00:30:43,359
What was said at that meeting?

553
00:30:43,442 --> 00:30:47,317
I was told the Youth International Party
would be holding a festival of life

554
00:30:47,400 --> 00:30:49,734
during the Democratic National Convention.

555
00:30:49,817 --> 00:30:52,150
There would be thousands
of young people attending

556
00:30:52,234 --> 00:30:54,275
and there'd be rock bands
playing in the park.

557
00:30:54,359 --> 00:30:55,650
Music will be performed.

558
00:30:55,734 --> 00:30:57,650
- Rock music?
- I would think.

559
00:30:57,734 --> 00:31:00,317
They also said
there would be public fornication.

560
00:31:00,400 --> 00:31:01,567
Say that again, sir?

561
00:31:01,650 --> 00:31:03,109
Public fornication.

562
00:31:03,192 --> 00:31:05,692
You're asking
for a Parks permit for public--

563
00:31:05,775 --> 00:31:07,025
- Yeah.
- And rock music.

564
00:31:07,109 --> 00:31:08,025
No, of course not.

565
00:31:08,109 --> 00:31:09,234
What if it was R&B?

566
00:31:09,317 --> 00:31:12,109
- Did you issue the permits?
- No, I did not.

567
00:31:12,692 --> 00:31:17,567
And what, if anything, did Abbie Hoffman
say when you denied their request?

568
00:31:17,650 --> 00:31:19,942
Mr. Stahl, you need
to understand something.

569
00:31:20,025 --> 00:31:24,609
There's gonna be a festival of life
in Grant Park held during the convention.

570
00:31:24,692 --> 00:31:28,442
Bands will play rock music.
There will be public fornication.

571
00:31:28,525 --> 00:31:31,275
Likely some of it with the wives
and mistresses of delegates.

572
00:31:31,359 --> 00:31:35,150
Psychedelic, long-haired leftists
will consort with dope users.

573
00:31:35,734 --> 00:31:38,359
And we'll insist that
the next president of the US

574
00:31:38,442 --> 00:31:40,609
stops sending our friends
to be slaughtered.

575
00:31:40,692 --> 00:31:43,109
This will happen
whether you give us the permit or not.

576
00:31:43,192 --> 00:31:45,775
Hotels will be filled with delegates.
Where will people sleep?

577
00:31:45,859 --> 00:31:48,525
Some will sleep in tents,
others will live frivolously.

578
00:31:48,609 --> 00:31:50,567
- How many people are coming?
- A lot.

579
00:31:50,650 --> 00:31:53,942
What's a lot? A thousand? Two thousand?

580
00:31:54,025 --> 00:31:55,025
Ten thousand.

581
00:31:55,109 --> 00:31:57,234
- Jesus Christ.
- Right?

582
00:31:58,025 --> 00:32:01,150
Did Abbie Hoffman add anything
at the end of the meeting?

583
00:32:01,234 --> 00:32:02,234
Yes.

584
00:32:02,275 --> 00:32:04,067
- What did he say?
- He said...

585
00:32:04,150 --> 00:32:06,984
Or you give me 100 grand
and I could call the whole thing off.

586
00:32:07,067 --> 00:32:08,109
Thank you.

587
00:32:09,609 --> 00:32:11,109
Mr. Fineglass.

588
00:32:11,192 --> 00:32:12,984
Uh, Weinglass, sir.

589
00:32:14,400 --> 00:32:18,484
Mr. Stahl, the meeting you just described
with Mr. Hoffman and Mr. Rubin,

590
00:32:18,567 --> 00:32:21,734
was that the only meeting you had
with any of the defendants?

591
00:32:21,817 --> 00:32:22,817
No.

592
00:32:22,859 --> 00:32:26,525
On August 2nd, you had a meeting
with Tom Hayden and Rennie Davis.

593
00:32:26,609 --> 00:32:29,109
- Tom Hayden.
- Rennie Davis.

594
00:32:29,192 --> 00:32:31,942
On August 12th,
you had a meeting with David Dellinger.

595
00:32:32,484 --> 00:32:34,400
I'll tell you the same thing
I told the others.

596
00:32:34,484 --> 00:32:37,025
There were two more meetings
with Tom and Rennie

597
00:32:37,109 --> 00:32:39,317
on the 10th and 12th of August,

598
00:32:39,400 --> 00:32:43,025
and one more meeting
with David Dellinger on the 26th.

599
00:32:43,109 --> 00:32:44,275
I can't be sure of the dates.

600
00:32:44,359 --> 00:32:47,609
Well, I can be sure.
They're recorded in the log at City Hall.

601
00:32:47,692 --> 00:32:48,692
Okay...

602
00:32:48,734 --> 00:32:52,817
And in each of the meetings,
a request was made for a permit

603
00:32:52,900 --> 00:32:55,692
to demonstrate in Grant Park
during the convention.

604
00:32:55,775 --> 00:32:58,942
Mr. Stahl, we intend a peaceful demonstration.

605
00:32:59,025 --> 00:33:02,025
We're not interested in violence
or disturbing the delegates.

606
00:33:02,109 --> 00:33:05,942
And in each of the meetings,
the request for permits was denied.

607
00:33:06,025 --> 00:33:08,900
Listen, I'll tell you the same thing
I told Mr. Hoffman

608
00:33:08,984 --> 00:33:10,775
and Mr. Rubin and Mr. Dellinger.

609
00:33:10,859 --> 00:33:13,067
No demonstrations
within sight of the Hilton.

610
00:33:13,150 --> 00:33:16,025
We have to demonstrate there.
That's where the convention is.

611
00:33:16,109 --> 00:33:18,734
There will be no demonstrations
within sight of the Hilton.

612
00:33:18,817 --> 00:33:21,067
Okay.
But the thing is, there will be.

613
00:33:21,984 --> 00:33:24,275
- Are you threatening me, Mr. Hayden?
- No.

614
00:33:24,359 --> 00:33:26,817
We're not threatening you.
We're cautioning you.

615
00:33:26,900 --> 00:33:28,734
Thousands of people are coming to Chicago.

616
00:33:28,817 --> 00:33:30,817
If they're not given
a place to demonstrate,

617
00:33:30,900 --> 00:33:32,817
they'll demonstrate wherever they stand.

618
00:33:32,900 --> 00:33:35,025
So it's reckless, irresponsible,

619
00:33:35,109 --> 00:33:38,150
and foolishly dangerous of the city
not to have a contingency plan.

620
00:33:38,234 --> 00:33:40,650
We're gonna need
police security, first aid...

621
00:33:40,734 --> 00:33:42,442
- Traffic control.
- Water, sanitation.

622
00:33:42,525 --> 00:33:47,109
So, five times,
you were asked for a permit.

623
00:33:47,192 --> 00:33:50,109
Five times,
you were advised of the dangers

624
00:33:50,192 --> 00:33:52,650
of not providing
a location to demonstrate--

625
00:33:52,734 --> 00:33:55,025
I don't take my instructions
from the defendants.

626
00:33:55,109 --> 00:33:56,469
- No, you don't.
- I don't.

627
00:33:56,525 --> 00:33:58,067
You take them from Mayor Daley.

628
00:33:59,484 --> 00:34:02,109
You're appointed by the mayor
and you serve at his pleasure?

629
00:34:02,192 --> 00:34:03,025
Yes.

630
00:34:03,109 --> 00:34:06,234
And you're subject to removal
in the same manner by the mayor?

631
00:34:06,817 --> 00:34:08,817
- Yes.
- Thank you.

632
00:34:08,900 --> 00:34:11,775
Further cross-examination, Mr. Kunstler.

633
00:34:11,859 --> 00:34:14,400
Yes, sir. Mr. Stahl. When Abbie--

634
00:34:14,484 --> 00:34:15,650
Excuse me.

635
00:34:15,734 --> 00:34:20,359
Mr. Seale, would you identify
the man sitting behind you?

636
00:34:21,359 --> 00:34:22,859
- No, sir.
- No?

637
00:34:22,942 --> 00:34:24,109
- That's right.
- Why not?

638
00:34:24,192 --> 00:34:25,859
He's not on trial here.

639
00:34:25,942 --> 00:34:31,109
Mr. Seale, identify the man behind you.

640
00:34:35,192 --> 00:34:36,275
His name is Fred Hampton.

641
00:34:36,359 --> 00:34:37,859
Let the record indicate

642
00:34:37,942 --> 00:34:42,025
that Mr. Hampton is head of the Chicago
chapter of the Black Panther Party.

643
00:34:42,109 --> 00:34:46,275
Your Honor, Mr. Hampton isn't at the bar.
Why is the record identifying him at all?

644
00:34:46,359 --> 00:34:49,609
Mr. Hampton is clearly
giving Mr. Seale legal advice.

645
00:34:49,692 --> 00:34:51,942
My lawyer is Charles Garry.

646
00:34:52,025 --> 00:34:53,567
Excuse me, sir, but for all you know,

647
00:34:53,650 --> 00:34:56,609
Mr. Hampton is giving Mr. Seale
the score of the White Sox game.

648
00:34:56,692 --> 00:34:58,984
- I will assume that he is not.
- Why?

649
00:34:59,067 --> 00:35:02,942
Because that's what happens
when you don't have a lawyer.

650
00:35:03,025 --> 00:35:06,400
The court assumes
that you are being represented

651
00:35:06,484 --> 00:35:09,484
by the Black Panther sitting behind you.

652
00:35:12,775 --> 00:35:13,775
Continue.

653
00:35:14,400 --> 00:35:19,317
Mr. Stahl, when Abbie offered
to call the whole thing off for $100,000,

654
00:35:19,400 --> 00:35:23,692
did you think that he was serious
or did you think he was making a joke?

655
00:35:23,775 --> 00:35:26,609
I had no reason
not to think he was serious.

656
00:35:26,692 --> 00:35:29,317
- Really? Do you know what extortion is?
- Yes.

657
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:30,984
- Do you know it's a felony?
- Yes.

658
00:35:31,067 --> 00:35:33,109
Okay. So, when you called the FBI

659
00:35:33,192 --> 00:35:36,900
and told 'em about Mr. Hoffman's attempt
to extort a government employee,

660
00:35:36,984 --> 00:35:38,942
- what'd they say?
- I didn't call the FBI.

661
00:35:39,025 --> 00:35:42,109
Sorry. When you called the US attorney
and reported attempted extortion,

662
00:35:42,192 --> 00:35:44,525
- what'd their office say?
- I didn't call the US att--

663
00:35:44,609 --> 00:35:47,025
- Cooke County DA. Did you call them?
- No, sir.

664
00:35:47,109 --> 00:35:48,984
- The chief of police?
- Mr. Kunstler--

665
00:35:49,067 --> 00:35:51,609
The police officer posted
outside the mayor's office?

666
00:35:51,692 --> 00:35:55,067
How about the mayor?
Mr. Stahl, I'm gonna ask you again.

667
00:35:55,650 --> 00:36:01,442
When Abbie Hoffman asked
for $100,000 to call the whole thing off,

668
00:36:01,525 --> 00:36:05,984
did you think that he was serious
or did you know that he was making a joke?

669
00:36:06,067 --> 00:36:08,942
I had no reason
not to believe he was serious.

670
00:36:09,025 --> 00:36:12,317
Then, along with extortion,
did you know that perjury is a crime?

671
00:36:12,400 --> 00:36:14,692
- Objection.
- Sustained, and strike it.

672
00:36:14,775 --> 00:36:15,692
In fact,

673
00:36:15,775 --> 00:36:19,859
strike the entirety of Mr. Stahl's
testimony under cross-examination,

674
00:36:19,942 --> 00:36:22,734
and the jury is instructed
to disregard it.

675
00:36:22,817 --> 00:36:25,775
You're gonna strike
the entire cross-examination?

676
00:36:25,859 --> 00:36:28,650
I gave you
and co-counsel Fineglass ample--

677
00:36:28,734 --> 00:36:30,650
Co-counsel's name is Weinglass.

678
00:36:30,734 --> 00:36:34,109
Mr. Stahl's testimony
under cross-examination is entirely--

679
00:36:34,192 --> 00:36:36,817
You are interrupting
the court again, Mr. Kunstler.

680
00:36:36,900 --> 00:36:38,734
Move to reinstate testimony.

681
00:36:38,817 --> 00:36:40,025
Overruled.

682
00:36:45,192 --> 00:36:47,150
- Overruled.
- Exception.

683
00:36:47,234 --> 00:36:49,900
Noted.
Are there any further questions?

684
00:36:50,525 --> 00:36:53,692
Yes. So, Mr. Stahl,
in any of these meetings,

685
00:36:53,775 --> 00:36:57,359
did any of the defendants say
that if you didn't grant them permits,

686
00:36:57,442 --> 00:36:59,942
that they would do
violent acts to the city?

687
00:37:00,025 --> 00:37:05,484
Yes, they said the Parks permit should be
issued in order to minimize destruction.

688
00:37:05,567 --> 00:37:08,317
Did they indicate from whom
this destruction would come?

689
00:37:09,025 --> 00:37:12,025
The destruction did not come
from the Chicago Police Department,

690
00:37:12,109 --> 00:37:13,859
if that's what you're suggesting.

691
00:37:15,192 --> 00:37:16,400
No further questions.

692
00:37:17,650 --> 00:37:19,734
I'd like to cross-examine
the witness, Your Honor.

693
00:37:19,817 --> 00:37:21,567
- You may not.
- Have you met me?

694
00:37:21,650 --> 00:37:22,817
Sit, Mr. Seale.

695
00:37:28,775 --> 00:37:30,484
Are you guilty of conspiracy?

696
00:37:30,567 --> 00:37:32,609
We believe that we are innocent.

697
00:37:32,692 --> 00:37:36,400
The people who are guilty of conspiracy
are the fuckers who put us on trial.

698
00:37:36,484 --> 00:37:40,025
They are responsible for the bloodshed
that flowed in the streets of Chicago.

699
00:37:40,109 --> 00:37:42,525
Why won't Bobby Seale
let anyone represent him?

700
00:37:42,609 --> 00:37:44,984
You've posed that question
in the form of a lie.

701
00:37:53,484 --> 00:37:55,400
Conspiracy Office.
Can you hold on?

702
00:37:57,900 --> 00:37:59,942
Conspiracy Office.
Can you hold on?

703
00:38:05,775 --> 00:38:07,734
Conspiracy Office.
Can you hold on?

704
00:38:07,817 --> 00:38:11,317
Maybe you don't want to call it the,
uh, Conspiracy Office.

705
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:13,400
They understand irony
and appreciate the humor.

706
00:38:13,484 --> 00:38:16,067
- I wouldn't count on it.
- Most people are smart, Bill.

707
00:38:16,150 --> 00:38:19,567
If you believe that, you'll get your
heart broken every day of your life.

708
00:38:19,650 --> 00:38:23,067
