Mr. Kunstler, the demonstrators
attacked the police

1182
01:04:57,567 --> 01:04:58,900
and the police responded.

1183
01:05:00,400 --> 01:05:04,484
And are any of those demonstrators
that you saw attacking the police

1184
01:05:04,567 --> 01:05:06,859
sitting here at the defense table?

1185
01:05:06,942 --> 01:05:09,567
- No, sir.
- Well, thank you.

1186
01:05:10,067 --> 01:05:11,984
No further questions.

1187
01:05:12,067 --> 01:05:14,067
- The court will stand--
- I wasn't there, either.

1188
01:05:14,150 --> 01:05:15,942
- Mr. Seale--
- I wasn't there at all.

1189
01:05:16,025 --> 01:05:18,317
I should be allowed
to cross-examine this witness!

1190
01:05:18,400 --> 01:05:20,984
- We will stand in recess until--
- Four hours!

1191
01:05:21,067 --> 01:05:22,067
Mr. Hampton!

1192
01:05:22,150 --> 01:05:24,025
That's how long Bobby Seale
was in Chicago.

1193
01:05:24,109 --> 01:05:25,692
- Quiet!
- Four hours!

1194
01:05:33,150 --> 01:05:34,359
All rise.

1195
01:05:39,317 --> 01:05:42,234
The court will stand in recess
for the weekend.

1196
01:05:49,359 --> 01:05:51,067
Yeah, I took in the exhibit.

1197
01:05:51,150 --> 01:05:52,984
I cleared my mind.

1198
01:05:54,442 --> 01:05:57,109
Stood there for 20 minutes.
I felt nothing.

1199
01:05:58,942 --> 01:06:03,442
Well, but it wasn't a painting,
it was an exhibit.

1200
01:06:04,150 --> 01:06:05,609
It was a natural history museum.

1201
01:06:05,692 --> 01:06:08,609
And when you put exhibits
of Native Indian families

1202
01:06:08,692 --> 01:06:10,234
in a natural history museum

1203
01:06:10,317 --> 01:06:13,484
alongside dioramas of early man
and the Jurassic age,

1204
01:06:13,567 --> 01:06:18,317
it gives the impression that the Cherokee
evolved into modern-day Europeans.

1205
01:06:19,400 --> 01:06:20,525
Look who it is.

1206
01:06:21,109 --> 01:06:23,067
I got a bone to pick with that guy.

1207
01:06:23,150 --> 01:06:24,317
Hey, Counselor.

1208
01:06:25,692 --> 01:06:27,942
- No colleges this weekend?
- Winter break.

1209
01:06:28,025 --> 01:06:30,692
- My audience went home to their parents.
- Mm-hmm.

1210
01:06:30,775 --> 01:06:32,317
Are these ladies related to you?

1211
01:06:32,400 --> 01:06:34,775
These are my daughters.
This is Emily and Julie.

1212
01:06:34,859 --> 01:06:36,192
Your dad's a good guy.

1213
01:06:36,275 --> 01:06:39,234
That's coming from someone
who he's trying hard to put in prison.

1214
01:06:39,317 --> 01:06:41,275
We shouldn't be talking
without your lawyer.

1215
01:06:41,359 --> 01:06:42,609
We're all on the same team.

1216
01:06:43,234 --> 01:06:46,650
In a sense, I guess,
but in a much truer sense, we're not.

1217
01:06:46,734 --> 01:06:49,150
Girls, here, take this dollar

1218
01:06:49,234 --> 01:06:52,900
and go over to those musicians
and put it in their hat, okay?

1219
01:06:52,984 --> 01:06:55,942
And here's a quarter.
Go buy some of those candy-coated peanuts

1220
01:06:56,025 --> 01:06:59,025
that your mom won't let you have.
All right? Shh.

1221
01:06:59,984 --> 01:07:01,859
- Sweet kids.
- Thank you.

1222
01:07:01,942 --> 01:07:06,525
If your lawyer were here, I'd tell you
the window's closing for you to plead out.

1223
01:07:07,109 --> 01:07:09,442
We're not taking a fuckin' deal.
Would you stop?

1224
01:07:10,025 --> 01:07:12,984
I wish I could share Abbie's sentiment
that you're a good guy,

1225
01:07:13,067 --> 01:07:14,234
but I'm afraid I can't.

1226
01:07:14,817 --> 01:07:16,317
I'm sorry to hear that.

1227
01:07:16,400 --> 01:07:20,317
Sending Daphne O'Connor
to break my heart was way out of line.

1228
01:07:20,400 --> 01:07:22,692
Well, I don't work for the FBI,

1229
01:07:22,775 --> 01:07:25,817
but O'Connor was one of many agents
sent to gather intelligence

1230
01:07:25,900 --> 01:07:27,859
on what had been deemed a credible threat.

1231
01:07:27,942 --> 01:07:31,984
Fine. Then you bug our phones,
you wire up a dope dealer. Be a man.

1232
01:07:32,067 --> 01:07:35,942
- You don't send a woman to ensorcell me.
- What?

1233
01:07:36,025 --> 01:07:37,734
- It means to enchant.
- Oh.

1234
01:07:37,817 --> 01:07:41,567
- Only to have her crush my soul.
- How long did you two know each other?

1235
01:07:42,150 --> 01:07:45,359
Ninety-three hours.
Could've been a lifetime.

1236
01:07:45,442 --> 01:07:47,567
For a fruit fly. Enjoy your weekend.

1237
01:07:47,650 --> 01:07:49,359
Is that even ethical?

1238
01:07:50,234 --> 01:07:51,567
Aren't there ethics rules?

1239
01:07:51,650 --> 01:07:53,192
Did she engage with you sexually?

1240
01:07:54,984 --> 01:07:56,734
Well, we were takin' it slow.

1241
01:07:57,692 --> 01:07:59,317
He's gonna be all right.

1242
01:07:59,400 --> 01:08:00,650
One egg is un oeuf?

1243
01:08:01,609 --> 01:08:04,234
- They teach her that at the Academy?
- Yep.

1244
01:08:04,317 --> 01:08:06,150
We don't have any beef with you.

1245
01:08:06,234 --> 01:08:09,192
We know you're doing your job
and you don't think we're criminals.

1246
01:08:09,275 --> 01:08:10,984
I'm not sure where you get that info,

1247
01:08:11,067 --> 01:08:13,775
but I represent the People
without passion or prejudice.

1248
01:08:14,359 --> 01:08:16,234
You think we were responsible?

1249
01:08:16,817 --> 01:08:18,609
You got the result you were looking for.

1250
01:08:19,525 --> 01:08:22,484
- So did Nixon.
- How 'bout that?

1251
01:08:23,442 --> 01:08:24,525
See you Monday.

1252
01:08:26,359 --> 01:08:27,650
Does she ever mention me?

1253
01:08:52,025 --> 01:08:53,192
Conspiracy Office.

1254
01:08:59,525 --> 01:09:00,525
I need a second.

1255
01:09:07,317 --> 01:09:08,650
Something's happened, Tom.

1256
01:09:28,984 --> 01:09:30,275
Bobby, uh...

1257
01:09:32,859 --> 01:09:35,650
Fred Hampton
was shot and killed last night.

1258
01:09:39,067 --> 01:09:43,234
There was a police raid,
and there was a shootout.

1259
01:09:43,942 --> 01:09:45,150
And he's dead.

1260
01:09:48,400 --> 01:09:51,067
- It took place between the hours of 4:00--
- I know.

1261
01:09:51,942 --> 01:09:54,692
- You were told?
- Yeah.

1262
01:09:54,775 --> 01:09:55,859
Um...

1263
01:09:57,150 --> 01:09:58,525
I'm so sorry.

1264
01:10:06,567 --> 01:10:09,317
The seven of you,
you've all got the same father, right?

1265
01:10:11,442 --> 01:10:12,942
I'm talkin' to you.

1266
01:10:15,150 --> 01:10:17,400
You all got the same father, right?

1267
01:10:17,484 --> 01:10:19,067
"Cut your hair...

1268
01:10:20,025 --> 01:10:25,317
don't be a fag, respect authority,
respect America, respect me."

1269
01:10:27,359 --> 01:10:30,984
Your life, it's a "fuck you"
to your father, right?

1270
01:10:33,150 --> 01:10:34,150
A little?

1271
01:10:36,067 --> 01:10:38,359
- Maybe.
- Maybe.

1272
01:10:39,025 --> 01:10:41,817
And you can see how that's different
from a rope on a tree?

1273
01:10:42,900 --> 01:10:43,900
Yeah.

1274
01:10:44,442 --> 01:10:45,442
Yeah.

1275
01:10:49,025 --> 01:10:50,900
He was shot in the shoulder first.

1276
01:10:52,692 --> 01:10:55,150
You can't aim a gun
if you've been shot in the shoulder.

1277
01:10:55,234 --> 01:10:56,775
You can't squeeze the trigger.

1278
01:10:58,025 --> 01:10:59,817
Second shot was in his head.

1279
01:11:02,317 --> 01:11:03,942
Fred was executed.

1280
01:11:08,650 --> 01:11:09,650
Anything else?

1281
01:11:13,900 --> 01:11:14,900
No.

1282
01:11:27,609 --> 01:11:31,359
Calling your attention
to the evening of the next day,

1283
01:11:31,442 --> 01:11:34,859
Tuesday, August 27th,
were you in Grant Park?

1284
01:11:34,942 --> 01:11:38,734
Yes. There was
a "Free Huey Newton" rally going on.

1285
01:11:38,817 --> 01:11:42,609
- WOMAN Recognize any of the speakers?
- I heard Jerry Rubin give a speech.

1286
01:11:42,692 --> 01:11:45,192
Phil Ochs sang,
and then Bobby Seale gave a speech.

1287
01:11:45,275 --> 01:11:48,942
I object to this testimony against me
because I have been denied counsel.

1288
01:11:50,067 --> 01:11:51,067
We understand.

1289
01:11:51,567 --> 01:11:54,234
Do you recall any of Mr. Seale's speech?

1290
01:11:54,317 --> 01:11:55,400
Yes. He said--

1291
01:11:55,484 --> 01:11:57,442
- I object to this man's--
- Quiet!

1292
01:11:58,359 --> 01:11:59,192
Go ahead.

1293
01:11:59,275 --> 01:12:01,817
- May I refer to notes?
- Yes.

1294
01:12:02,900 --> 01:12:07,109
He said, "We must
understand that as we go forth

1295
01:12:07,192 --> 01:12:09,150
to try to move
the reprobate politicians..."

1296
01:12:09,234 --> 01:12:10,067
Your Honor--

1297
01:12:10,150 --> 01:12:13,984
"...our cowardly Congress,
the jive, double-lip talking Nixon--"

1298
01:12:14,067 --> 01:12:16,317
"Jive, double-lip, talking Nixon..."

1299
01:12:16,400 --> 01:12:19,984
You're making me sound like
one funky cat. Thank you, sir.

1300
01:12:20,067 --> 01:12:22,192
Last warning, Mr. Seale.

1301
01:12:24,150 --> 01:12:25,775
Did he say anything else?

1302
01:12:25,859 --> 01:12:28,150
He said, "The revolution at this time

1303
01:12:28,234 --> 01:12:32,317
is directly connected
to organized guns in force."

1304
01:12:34,525 --> 01:12:35,525
No more questions.

1305
01:12:37,275 --> 01:12:41,150
Jive, double-lip talking.
Funky, funky cat.

1306
01:12:41,234 --> 01:12:43,775
Would the defense like
to cross-examine the witness?

1307
01:12:43,859 --> 01:12:48,150
Yes. I'm sittin' here saying that I would
like to cross-examine a witness.

1308
01:12:48,234 --> 01:12:51,150
- Only lawyers can address a witness.
- My lawyer is Charles Garry.

1309
01:12:51,234 --> 01:12:54,734
- I'm tired of hearing that.
- Couldn't care less what you're tired of.

1310
01:12:55,525 --> 01:12:56,525
What did you say?

1311
01:12:59,025 --> 01:13:04,109
I said it would be impossible for me
to care any less what you are tired of.

1312
01:13:04,192 --> 01:13:07,192
And I demand to cross-examine the witness.

1313
01:13:07,275 --> 01:13:09,400
Sit in your chair and be quiet.

1314
01:13:09,484 --> 01:13:13,109
And don't ever address this court
in that manner again.

1315
01:13:16,984 --> 01:13:18,650
Are there any further questions?

1316
01:13:20,734 --> 01:13:23,942
We'll stand in recess for one hour,
and court will resume again--

1317
01:13:24,025 --> 01:13:27,150
- It was premeditated murder!
- Yes, it was!

1318
01:13:27,234 --> 01:13:30,984
- Fred Hampton was assassinated last night!
- Marshals, put Mr. Seale--

1319
01:13:31,067 --> 01:13:33,025
He wouldn't have been able to hold a gun!

1320
01:13:33,109 --> 01:13:37,859
When they publish the coroner's report,
ask about the bullet in his shoulder!

1321
01:13:41,234 --> 01:13:44,359
I strongly caution you, Mr. Seale.

1322
01:13:45,192 --> 01:13:46,942
I strongly caution--

1323
01:13:47,025 --> 01:13:49,609
Oh, strongly fuck yourself!

1324
01:13:52,817 --> 01:13:55,025
Marshals, take that defendant into a room

1325
01:13:55,109 --> 01:13:57,692
and deal with him
as he should be dealt with.

1326
01:15:24,359 --> 01:15:29,317
Let the record show
that I tried, fairly and impartially.

1327
01:15:29,400 --> 01:15:33,400
I tried to get the defendant
to sit on his own.

1328
01:15:33,484 --> 01:15:35,692
I ask you again, Mr. Seale,

1329
01:15:35,775 --> 01:15:39,234
and you may indicate
by raising your head up and down,

1330
01:15:39,817 --> 01:15:42,067
or moving it from side to side,

1331
01:15:42,150 --> 01:15:47,525
if I have your assurance that you will
not do anything to disrupt this trial,

1332
01:15:47,609 --> 01:15:50,650
if I allow you to resume proper order.

1333
01:15:51,942 --> 01:15:54,025
Do I have your assurance?

1334
01:16:03,400 --> 01:16:05,109
Mr. Schultz, call your next witness.

1335
01:16:09,734 --> 01:16:10,942
Mr. Schultz?

1336
01:16:20,025 --> 01:16:21,234
Your Honor, may we approach?

1337
01:16:27,234 --> 01:16:28,484
Can he breathe?

1338
01:16:29,317 --> 01:16:31,192
Can you breathe all right, Bobby?

1339
01:16:37,609 --> 01:16:41,150
Your Honor, our defendant is gagged
and bound in an American courtroom.

1340
01:16:41,234 --> 01:16:43,109
He brought it on himself.

1341
01:16:43,192 --> 01:16:44,192
Are you insane?

1342
01:16:44,234 --> 01:16:45,359
Mr. Kunstler.

1343
01:16:46,942 --> 01:16:48,484
Love of God.

1344
01:16:49,400 --> 01:16:52,192
What do you want, Mr. Schultz?
This is your sidebar.

1345
01:16:52,275 --> 01:16:55,859
The government would like to make a motion
that Bobby Seale be separated--

1346
01:16:55,942 --> 01:16:57,942
- Wait, wait, wait--
- Sir, please.

1347
01:16:58,567 --> 01:17:01,525
A motion that Bobby Seale be separated
from the rest of the defendants

1348
01:17:01,609 --> 01:17:03,734
and his case be declared a mistrial.

1349
01:17:04,400 --> 01:17:06,192
You want me to give him his mistrial?

1350
01:17:06,275 --> 01:17:10,859
Of course, because you took that Black guy
and you made him a sympathetic character.

1351
01:17:10,942 --> 01:17:15,609
Mr. Kunstler, I have lived
a very long time, sir.

1352
01:17:15,692 --> 01:17:18,817
And you're the first person ever

1353
01:17:18,900 --> 01:17:23,192
to suggest that I have discriminated
against a Black man.

1354
01:17:23,275 --> 01:17:25,192
Then let the record show
that I am the second.

1355
01:17:28,400 --> 01:17:29,400
Step back.

1356
01:17:43,942 --> 01:17:48,109
I'm issuing an order declaring a mistrial
as to the defendant Bobby G. Seale.

1357
01:17:57,817 --> 01:18:02,692
Mr. Seale, you are currently charged
with 16 counts of contempt

1358
01:18:02,775 --> 01:18:05,775
for your repeated displays of disrespect,

1359
01:18:05,859 --> 01:18:09,692
and you have a pending homicide charge
in Connecticut.

1360
01:18:10,484 --> 01:18:15,150
You are not home free, sir,
and I doubt you ever will be.

1361
01:18:16,484 --> 01:18:20,650
We are adjourned until 10:00, Monday.

1362
01:18:20,734 --> 01:18:21,900
All rise.

1363
01:18:55,400 --> 01:18:57,484
Conspiracy Office, how can I help you?

1364
01:19:03,317 --> 01:19:05,442
No, sir. I am a white woman.

1365
01:19:09,192 --> 01:19:12,859
Yeah, I've slept with several
in my life so far, and on balance,

1366
01:19:12,942 --> 01:19:14,484
I'd have to say it is better.

1367
01:19:14,567 --> 01:19:16,942
I think that's a big part
of what's got you worked up.

1368
01:19:17,025 --> 01:19:17,859
Hang up the phone.

1369
01:19:17,942 --> 01:19:20,609
It's not so much that it's bigger.
It's just better.

1370
01:19:20,692 --> 01:19:21,692
Hang up the phone.

1371
01:19:24,109 --> 01:19:26,025
Was that a parting gift for Bobby?

1372
01:19:27,067 --> 01:19:29,609
No. That was just for me.

1373
01:19:43,067 --> 01:19:45,234
Why the fuck did you stand up?

1374
01:19:45,984 --> 01:19:46,859
It was a reflex.

1375
01:19:46,942 --> 01:19:48,734
He was respecting the institution.

1376
01:19:48,817 --> 01:19:52,900
I don't know what good it does to insult
the judge in view of the jury, the press,

1377
01:19:52,984 --> 01:19:56,359
and Foran and Schultz, who'll recommend
sentencing if we're convicted.

1378
01:19:56,442 --> 01:19:59,775
It's a revolution, Tom.
We may have to hurt somebody's feelings.

1379
01:20:02,234 --> 01:20:03,525
So, um...

1380
01:20:04,817 --> 01:20:06,400
we have this list.

1381
01:20:06,484 --> 01:20:09,942
Maybe Monday morning,
we could read the names into the record

1382
01:20:10,025 --> 01:20:11,150
as a way of saying--

1383
01:20:11,234 --> 01:20:12,067
Saying what?

1384
01:20:12,150 --> 01:20:16,442
That whatever we're facing, you know,
it's peanuts compared to what--

1385
01:20:16,525 --> 01:20:19,734
He's gonna sentence us.
The judge decides what we're facing.

1386
01:20:19,817 --> 01:20:22,650
- It is a goddamn trial.
- Political trial.

1387
01:20:22,734 --> 01:20:26,109
No, we were arrested... The law
doesn't recognize political trials.

1388
01:20:26,192 --> 01:20:29,067
No, we weren't arrested.
We were chosen.

1389
01:20:32,109 --> 01:20:35,567
Lee, John, have you guys asked yourselves
what you're doing here?

1390
01:20:35,650 --> 01:20:36,484
Every day.

1391
01:20:36,567 --> 01:20:38,067
You're a give-back.

1392
01:20:38,150 --> 01:20:40,692
They give the jury
a couple of guys they can acquit

1393
01:20:40,775 --> 01:20:43,567
so they feel better
about finding the rest of us guilty.

1394
01:20:46,567 --> 01:20:48,359
Lenny, am I wrong?

1395
01:20:49,734 --> 01:20:50,567
No.

1396
01:20:50,650 --> 01:20:54,650
Wait, so our role in history is that
we made it easier to convict our friends?

1397
01:20:54,734 --> 01:20:57,525
They're gonna find us guilty
if they just don't like you.

1398
01:20:57,609 --> 01:20:59,984
That's why Bill won't put us on the stand.

1399
01:21:00,067 --> 01:21:02,650
I can take the stand.
I'm easier for them to like.

1400
01:21:03,567 --> 01:21:05,609
I'm literally a Boy Scout troop leader.

1401
01:21:10,942 --> 01:21:13,275
You're a conscientious objector.

1402
01:21:13,359 --> 01:21:15,234
A lot of people
are conscientious objectors.

1403
01:21:15,317 --> 01:21:16,484
During World War II?

1404
01:21:16,567 --> 01:21:20,109
You sat out World War II.
Even I wanna punch you.

1405
01:21:20,192 --> 01:21:23,442
- We can talk about that.
- I'm looking forward to it.

1406
01:21:23,525 --> 01:21:25,192
I could take the stand.

1407
01:21:25,275 --> 01:21:27,900
Mr. Rubin, you ever taught a classroom
how to make a bomb?

1408
01:21:27,984 --> 01:21:30,900
Man, eighth graders are taught
how Oppenheimer made a bomb.

1409
01:21:30,984 --> 01:21:34,109
Not one you can build
with materials from Woolworth's.

1410
01:21:34,192 --> 01:21:35,609
You know what'd be ironic?

1411
01:21:36,400 --> 01:21:38,400
- What?
- I said, know what--

1412
01:21:38,484 --> 01:21:40,734
He heard you.
He's asking what would be ironic.

1413
01:21:40,817 --> 01:21:45,525
I was gonna say if John Mitchell did
all this just to get back at Ramsey Clark.

1414
01:21:45,609 --> 01:21:47,569
- For what?
- That thing, remember?

1415
01:21:47,650 --> 01:21:50,359
Outgoing cabinet members
are supposed to resign,

1416
01:21:50,442 --> 01:21:53,234
but Ramsey Clark didn't tender
his resignation till--

1417
01:21:53,317 --> 01:21:55,359
I read Mitchell
had a fit about that.

1418
01:21:55,442 --> 01:21:58,400
- Yeah.
- Did you read about that, Lenny?

1419
01:21:58,984 --> 01:21:59,984
Bill?

1420
01:22:00,942 --> 01:22:03,067
He was never even on our witness list.

1421
01:22:03,150 --> 01:22:04,150
Who?

1422
01:22:04,234 --> 01:22:08,817
- The first witness you put on the stand--
- If this was a political trial...

1423
01:22:09,650 --> 01:22:11,400
- Bernadine.
- Yeah.

1424
01:22:11,484 --> 01:22:13,775
I need my office to find Ramsey Clark.

1425
01:22:14,525 --> 01:22:17,275
And William Kunstler just showed up.

1426
01:22:32,400 --> 01:22:33,400
Len.

1427
01:22:38,275 --> 01:22:41,400
Maybe... I don't know,
does he have a Secret Service detail?

1428
01:22:41,484 --> 01:22:44,525
Nah, they're here for us.

1429
01:22:50,150 --> 01:22:52,442
He was the attorney general.
What do we do?

1430
01:22:52,525 --> 01:22:55,400
- We just ring the doorbell?
- Yeah, I guess so.

1431
01:22:56,942 --> 01:22:59,234
- You wanna do it?
- Just ring the damn...

1432
01:23:04,900 --> 01:23:08,109
Good morning, I'm Bill Kunstler.
Mr. Clark is expecting us.

1433
01:23:08,192 --> 01:23:09,192
Come in.

1434
01:23:14,025 --> 01:23:15,025
Good morning.

1435
01:23:19,984 --> 01:23:22,150
He's in his study at the end of the hall.

1436
01:23:22,734 --> 01:23:23,984
Can I get anyone coffee?

1437
01:23:24,067 --> 01:23:26,359
I tell you what, ma'am.
That sounds great.

1438
01:23:26,442 --> 01:23:27,775
Nothing for me. Thank you.

1439
01:23:28,609 --> 01:23:30,192
At the end of the hall.

1440
01:23:31,150 --> 01:23:32,359
Mr. Hayden?

1441
01:23:33,525 --> 01:23:36,734
I read in the paper you were
the only one who stood for the judge

1442
01:23:36,817 --> 01:23:38,400
after what he did to Bobby.

1443
01:23:40,109 --> 01:23:43,484
Uh, that was a mistake.
It was just a reflex.

1444
01:23:43,567 --> 01:23:44,567
Tom?

1445
01:23:55,734 --> 01:23:56,734
Hey, Bill.

1446
01:23:58,400 --> 01:23:59,567
Ramsey Clark.

1447
01:24:00,442 --> 01:24:01,775
Pleased to meet you, sir.

1448
01:24:03,067 --> 01:24:05,234
This is Leonard Weinglass.

1449
01:24:05,317 --> 01:24:07,567
- Mr. Weinglass.
- And Tom Hayden.

1450
01:24:07,650 --> 01:24:09,192
Oh, I know who Tom Hayden is.

1451
01:24:09,275 --> 01:24:11,525
The FBI used to work for me.

1452
01:24:12,775 --> 01:24:16,317
Those two men, they're senior deputies
with the Justice Department.

1453
01:24:16,400 --> 01:24:17,734
Mr. Kelly and Mr. Ackerman.

1454
01:24:19,150 --> 01:24:22,067
- I don't know why these men are here.
- I invited them.

1455
01:24:22,650 --> 01:24:23,525
You invited them?

1456
01:24:23,609 --> 01:24:26,150
I don't want
the appearance of impropriety.

1457
01:24:26,234 --> 01:24:27,734
There isn't any impropriety.

1458
01:24:27,817 --> 01:24:30,025
And now there are witnesses to that.

1459
01:24:30,109 --> 01:24:34,859
Sir, these men are gonna call
Schultz and Foran as soon as we're done.

1460
01:24:34,942 --> 01:24:38,234
Don't be ridiculous.
They already called Schultz and Foran.

1461
01:24:38,317 --> 01:24:41,484
And they're gonna call John Mitchell
as soon as we're done here.

1462
01:24:42,109 --> 01:24:43,775
Go ahead, ask what you wanna ask.

1463
01:24:45,067 --> 01:24:47,400
- In front of them?
- Yeah.

1464
01:24:51,234 --> 01:24:52,234
All right.

1465
01:24:53,192 --> 01:24:57,359
Mr. Clark, while you were
attorney general for President Johnson

1466
01:24:57,442 --> 01:24:59,609
was there ever any discussion
with the White House

1467
01:24:59,692 --> 01:25:01,859
about seeking indictments
against my clients?

1468
01:25:01,942 --> 01:25:03,775
- He can't answer that.
- Why not?

1469
01:25:03,859 --> 01:25:04,859
It's against the law.

1470
01:25:04,942 --> 01:25:08,025
That's an overly broad
interpretation of the law.

1471
01:25:08,109 --> 01:25:09,984
- If you'd like--
- I'll tell you what.

1472
01:25:10,067 --> 01:25:12,275
We've dealt with
jury tampering, wiretapping,

1473
01:25:12,359 --> 01:25:14,525
a defendant that was literally gagged,

1474
01:25:14,609 --> 01:25:17,275
and a judge who's been
handing down rulings from the bench

1475
01:25:17,359 --> 01:25:19,609
that would be
considered wrong in Honduras.

1476
01:25:19,692 --> 01:25:23,900
So I'm a little less interested in the law
than I was when this trial began.

1477
01:25:23,984 --> 01:25:29,359
Well, whether you like the law or not,
as former AG, he is protected by it.

1478
01:25:29,442 --> 01:25:31,150
No, you are protected by it.

1479
01:25:32,150 --> 01:25:34,817
And with respect, sir, I can subpoena you.

1480
01:25:34,900 --> 01:25:37,734
Find a judge in this circuit
who will sign that subpoena.

1481
01:25:37,817 --> 01:25:41,567
He's right. And taking the stand
voluntarily would be a big risk for me.

1482
01:25:42,150 --> 01:25:43,900
Well, again, with due respect, sir,

1483
01:25:43,984 --> 01:25:47,359
my clients take
a much bigger risk when they...

1484
01:25:48,067 --> 01:25:50,984
- stand against an enormous power...
- What took you so long?

1485
01:25:51,067 --> 01:25:53,692
...that they can't even see, and that...

1486
01:25:54,650 --> 01:25:57,067
I'm sorry.
What took me so long to do what?

1487
01:25:57,150 --> 01:25:59,109
To realize I'm your star witness.

1488
01:26:02,025 --> 01:26:04,692
- We were remarking upon that ourselves--
- Bill...

1489
01:26:04,775 --> 01:26:05,984
He can't testify.

1490
01:26:06,067 --> 01:26:08,442
I'm in private practice now.

1491
01:26:08,525 --> 01:26:11,192
And if John Mitchell
wants to cut me in half,

1492
01:26:11,275 --> 01:26:12,900
he can and he will.

1493
01:26:12,984 --> 01:26:14,484
You have to find some...

1494
01:26:15,734 --> 01:26:17,900
Sir, you have to find some courage now...

1495
01:26:19,192 --> 01:26:21,942
- And--
- Find some courage? Yeah.

1496
01:26:22,025 --> 01:26:24,692
Yes.
You have to find some courage and--

1497
01:26:24,775 --> 01:26:25,775
Tom.

1498
01:26:29,567 --> 01:26:32,025
That's what those two men came to tell me,

1499
01:26:32,109 --> 01:26:36,067
that if John Mitchell wants to
cut me in half, he can and he will.

1500
01:26:36,650 --> 01:26:40,817
So I wanted them in the room when I said,

1501
01:26:41,692 --> 01:26:43,025
"When do you want me in court?"

1502
01:26:45,817 --> 01:26:46,942
Mr. Clark?

1503
01:26:47,567 --> 01:26:48,567
I'm sorry?

1504
01:26:49,109 --> 01:26:50,442
Swear me in, Bill.

1505
01:26:50,525 --> 01:26:54,984
It is against the law for you to testify,
Ramsey. It is as simple as that.

1506
01:26:55,775 --> 01:26:57,067
It's General Clark.

1507
01:26:57,775 --> 01:26:59,942
And arrest me or shut the fuck up.

1508
01:27:05,317 --> 01:27:06,359
Found some.

1509
01:27:08,484 --> 01:27:11,025
Your Honor, the People move
to disallow this witness.

1510
01:27:11,109 --> 01:27:14,067
I'm sure the defense anticipated that.

1511
01:27:14,150 --> 01:27:16,109
Code of federal regulations mandates

1512
01:27:16,192 --> 01:27:18,484
the disclosure
of Justice Department materials

1513
01:27:18,567 --> 01:27:21,609
is prohibited without prior knowledge
of the attorney general,

1514
01:27:21,692 --> 01:27:24,650
plainly meaning
the sitting attorney general,

1515
01:27:24,734 --> 01:27:27,567
who is John Mitchell,
who has denied his approval.

1516
01:27:27,650 --> 01:27:32,525
Judge, the rule refers only to
very specific documents and information.

1517
01:27:32,609 --> 01:27:36,317
If the regulation were interpreted
as Mr. Schultz is asking it to be,

1518
01:27:36,400 --> 01:27:38,234
nobody in the federal government

1519
01:27:38,317 --> 01:27:41,734
could ever testify in any trial
after they left their job.

1520
01:27:43,859 --> 01:27:46,567
I think the government
is at least justified

1521
01:27:46,650 --> 01:27:50,150
in asking the defense
to demonstrate, by voir dire,

1522
01:27:50,234 --> 01:27:53,067
the testimony it expects
to elicit from the witness.

1523
01:27:53,150 --> 01:27:56,900
You'd like us to question the witness,
this witness,

1524
01:27:56,984 --> 01:27:59,817
outside the presence of the jury?

1525
01:27:59,900 --> 01:28:04,400
If I find any of the testimony relevant,
I'll call the jury back in to hear it.

1526
01:28:05,359 --> 01:28:07,067
Take it or leave it, Mr. Kunstler.

1527
01:28:10,442 --> 01:28:12,734
Defense calls Ramsey Clark.

1528
01:28:25,817 --> 01:28:26,900
State your name.

1529
01:28:27,400 --> 01:28:30,609
- William Ramsey Clark.
- Do you swear the testimony you give

1530
01:28:30,692 --> 01:28:33,234
will be the truth, the whole truth
and nothing but the truth?

1531
01:28:33,317 --> 01:28:34,317
I do.

1532
01:28:37,275 --> 01:28:42,692
Mr. Clark, what was your occupation
in the summer of 1968?

1533
01:28:42,775 --> 01:28:45,150
I was the attorney general
of the United States.

1534
01:28:45,234 --> 01:28:47,775
- You were appointed by President Johnson?
- Yes.

1535
01:28:47,859 --> 01:28:51,192
- Confirmed by the United States Senate.
- Yes.

1536
01:28:51,275 --> 01:28:56,525
Now, did you receive a phone call
at your office at 11:50 a.m.,

1537
01:28:56,609 --> 01:28:59,025
on September 10th of last year?

1538
01:28:59,109 --> 01:28:59,942
Yes.

1539
01:29:00,025 --> 01:29:02,192
- And from whom was that call?
- President Johnson.

1540
01:29:02,275 --> 01:29:07,734
Will you state what President Johnson
said to you and what was said to him?

1541
01:29:07,817 --> 01:29:10,109
Your Honor, at this point, we will object.

1542
01:29:10,192 --> 01:29:13,859
A cabinet officer does not have to,
and should not have to relate the contents

1543
01:29:13,942 --> 01:29:17,234
of a private call he had
with the president.

1544
01:29:17,317 --> 01:29:18,984
I'll sustain the objection.

1545
01:29:19,067 --> 01:29:22,442
Please, the court...
This is voir dire.

1546
01:29:22,525 --> 01:29:25,150
I thought objections were reserved.

1547
01:29:25,234 --> 01:29:28,275
There's a question of
attorney-client privilege to consider.

1548
01:29:28,359 --> 01:29:31,192
The president isn't a client
of the attorney general.

1549
01:29:34,859 --> 01:29:36,109
Excuse me, sir?

1550
01:29:36,692 --> 01:29:39,734
The president isn't a client
of the attorney general.

1551
01:29:39,817 --> 01:29:40,817
I'm happy to answer.

1552
01:29:40,900 --> 01:29:42,359
Your Honor...

1553
01:29:44,359 --> 01:29:47,817
Hearing from the witness
on this point is highly irregular.

1554
01:29:49,025 --> 01:29:51,817
Well, gentlemen, um...

1555
01:29:53,567 --> 01:29:55,067
This is my courtroom.

1556
01:29:55,817 --> 01:29:59,484
But the witness is the former, uh...

1557
01:29:59,567 --> 01:30:03,150
He's just stated
his willingness, you know,

1558
01:30:03,234 --> 01:30:07,275
so, for the purposes of voir dire,
I'll hear the answer.

1559
01:30:08,317 --> 01:30:09,317
Thank you.

1560
01:30:09,942 --> 01:30:15,525
Mr. Clark, uh, did President Johnson
ask you a question in that phone call?

1561
01:30:16,400 --> 01:30:19,984
The president asked me
if I intended to seek any indictments

1562
01:30:20,067 --> 01:30:23,484
related to the riots
the previous month in Chicago.

1563
01:30:24,400 --> 01:30:25,900
And what did you tell him?

1564
01:30:25,984 --> 01:30:28,567
I told him we wouldn't be
seeking indictments.

1565
01:30:28,650 --> 01:30:30,192
And can you tell us why?

1566
01:30:30,275 --> 01:30:34,692
An investigation by our criminal division
led to the conclusion

1567
01:30:34,775 --> 01:30:37,484
that the riots were started
by the Chicago Police Department.

1568
01:30:52,734 --> 01:30:56,317
And, Mr. Clark,
did your counterintelligence division

1569
01:30:56,400 --> 01:30:57,984
make a report as well?

1570
01:30:58,067 --> 01:31:01,942
They concluded that there was
no conspiracy by the defendants

1571
01:31:02,025 --> 01:31:04,942
to incite violence during the convention.

1572
01:31:05,025 --> 01:31:07,234
And then what happened
on the first Tuesday,

1573
01:31:07,317 --> 01:31:09,859
after the first Monday,
in November of that year?

1574
01:31:09,942 --> 01:31:12,359
- Richard Nixon was elected president.
- Sustained.

1575
01:31:12,442 --> 01:31:14,317
- Nobody objected--
- We do.

1576
01:31:14,400 --> 01:31:16,984
It's well-known there's no love lost
between the witness

1577
01:31:17,067 --> 01:31:18,609
and the sitting attorney general.

1578
01:31:18,692 --> 01:31:21,067
This witness was called to wage
a political attack

1579
01:31:21,150 --> 01:31:23,234
and should not be allowed before the jury.

1580
01:31:23,317 --> 01:31:24,150
Mr. Kunstler.

1581
01:31:24,234 --> 01:31:26,525
Your Honor, you cannot
possibly be considering

1582
01:31:26,609 --> 01:31:29,900
not allowing the jury to hear
what we've just heard?

1583
01:31:29,984 --> 01:31:32,025
The witness can't present them testimony

1584
01:31:32,109 --> 01:31:34,900
that would assist in making
a determination of guilt or innocence.

1585
01:31:34,984 --> 01:31:38,484
He just testified his own Justice
Department came to the conclusion--

1586
01:31:38,567 --> 01:31:40,150
The current Justice Department,

1587
01:31:40,234 --> 01:31:42,275
the one that matters,
came to a new conclusion.

1588
01:31:42,359 --> 01:31:46,150
Therefore, motivation of the prosecution
has to be called into question.

1589
01:31:46,234 --> 01:31:49,734
The motivation of the prosecution
is not an issue in a courtroom.

1590
01:31:49,817 --> 01:31:53,734
In any courtroom I've ever been in,
except this one.

1591
01:31:53,817 --> 01:31:54,817
Object.

1592
01:31:54,900 --> 01:31:57,442
Mr. Kunstler, do you have
any further examination

1593
01:31:57,525 --> 01:32:01,567
that will demonstrate that this witness
will make a material contribution,

1594
01:32:01,650 --> 01:32:04,275
or should I just ask him to step down?

1595
01:32:04,359 --> 01:32:06,359
You've ruled.

1596
01:32:10,234 --> 01:32:13,442
You're not gonna let the jury
hear his testimony.

1597
01:32:13,525 --> 01:32:16,025
Not unless you can demonstrate to me,

1598
01:32:16,109 --> 01:32:18,817
which you have not thus far done,
that this witness--

1599
01:32:18,900 --> 01:32:22,025
- Are you any good?
- Are you addressing the court reporter?

1600
01:32:22,109 --> 01:32:23,567
- Keep up with us.
- Mr. Kunstler--

1601
01:32:23,650 --> 01:32:25,359
Is this prosecution politically motivated?

1602
01:32:25,442 --> 01:32:26,942
- Object!
- Yes.

1603
01:32:27,025 --> 01:32:29,109
President Nixon inherited
an unpopular war.

1604
01:32:29,192 --> 01:32:30,442
- Yes.
- Step down, Mr. Clark.

1605
01:32:30,525 --> 01:32:32,859
And your clients make it
more unpopular every day.

1606
01:32:32,942 --> 01:32:37,609
This administration is paranoid
about the SDS, the Mobe, the New Left...

1607
01:32:37,692 --> 01:32:39,650
Mr. Clark, please.

1608
01:32:40,359 --> 01:32:44,775
Please, sir. I will be forced
to find you in contempt.

1609
01:32:45,400 --> 01:32:46,609
Do you understand?

1610
01:32:49,234 --> 01:32:50,234
I do, Your Honor.

1611
01:32:50,692 --> 01:32:52,609
Then step down, please.

1612
01:32:56,275 --> 01:32:57,442
Thank you, sir.

1613
01:33:06,609 --> 01:33:08,359
Just get to work on the appeal.

1614
01:33:18,525 --> 01:33:21,234
Your Honor, when the jury returns,

1615
01:33:22,400 --> 01:33:26,234
will they be informed
that the defense had called

1616
01:33:26,317 --> 01:33:29,400
the former attorney general
of the United States of America,

1617
01:33:29,484 --> 01:33:33,234
but this court ruled
that he couldn't testify?

1618
01:33:34,025 --> 01:33:36,234
No, that motion will be denied.

1619
01:33:56,025 --> 01:33:59,567
Cite Mr. Kunstler
with his third count of contempt.

1620
01:34:05,859 --> 01:34:07,109
You're a thug.

1621
01:34:07,192 --> 01:34:09,400
Did one of the defendants speak?

1622
01:34:09,484 --> 01:34:13,275
I did. I said you're a thug,
because you are.

1623
01:34:13,359 --> 01:34:15,109
- Dave.
- Please sit, Mr. Dellinger.

1624
01:34:15,192 --> 01:34:17,650
- If we're guilty, why not give us a trial?
- Dave.

1625
01:34:17,734 --> 01:34:19,359
Marshals, seat the defendant.

1626
01:34:19,442 --> 01:34:22,734
If we're guilty,
which you have clearly decided--

1627
01:34:22,817 --> 01:34:24,317
- Dave, I've got--
- Watch yourself.

1628
01:34:24,400 --> 01:34:26,692
You've clearly decided
that we were, why not--

1629
01:34:26,775 --> 01:34:29,317
No. You don't...
No, you don't need to grab my arm.

1630
01:34:32,984 --> 01:34:34,942
If we're guilty,
why not give us a trial?

1631
01:34:35,025 --> 01:34:38,525
I mean, I have sat here for six months
and watched you!

1632
01:34:38,609 --> 01:34:40,942
You don't need to grab my arm.

1633
01:34:41,025 --> 01:34:43,234
I have watched you.
I've watched you--

1634
01:34:43,317 --> 01:34:44,317
Sir--

1635
01:34:47,150 --> 01:34:49,525
It's okay.
He would not hurt a fly.

1636
01:34:49,609 --> 01:34:51,192
Take him out of here.
Lock him up.

1637
01:34:54,650 --> 01:34:55,859
I hit him.

1638
01:34:57,609 --> 01:34:58,859
I'm sorry.

1639
01:35:08,025 --> 01:35:09,067
I'm sorry.

1640
01:35:42,942 --> 01:35:45,775
There's only one thing.
There's one thing to do.

1641
01:35:46,484 --> 01:35:47,859
Solidarity with Dave.

1642
01:35:49,567 --> 01:35:52,275
Tomorrow, we go into court
and get ourselves arrested.

1643
01:35:53,192 --> 01:35:54,525
We're already arrested.

1644
01:35:55,234 --> 01:35:57,525
Is Bill talking to you
about taking the stand?

1645
01:35:58,150 --> 01:36:01,025
The press guys are saying
Bill's been talking to you about it.

1646
01:36:01,109 --> 01:36:02,442
He's been talking about it.

1647
01:36:02,525 --> 01:36:05,817
He thinks you might get the crowd
worked up with a position paper?

1648
01:36:05,900 --> 01:36:09,400
Maybe he thinks I won't try
to get the crowd worked up at all.

1649
01:36:09,984 --> 01:36:13,650
Maybe he thinks there are jurors
who relied on the safety of the police

1650
01:36:13,734 --> 01:36:15,900
and are put off
when someone calls them pigs,

1651
01:36:15,984 --> 01:36:18,400
or maybe he wants a witness
who dresses like a grown man.

1652
01:36:18,484 --> 01:36:24,025
The cops in this city
in the summer of 1968 were pigs.

1653
01:36:24,609 --> 01:36:26,734
I wonder how many of them
had kids in Vietnam.

1654
01:36:28,609 --> 01:36:30,442
He's gonna take the stand, not you?

1655
01:36:30,525 --> 01:36:32,275
And we're okay with that?

1656
01:36:33,900 --> 01:36:34,734
Abbie?

1657
